Ah yes, this would be why the group with the ranger in it is getting all the xp on most of our raids. I don't have a problem with it, as well, archery is quite superior to melee damage.<br>
<br>
I do however think that rangers should be getting the right amount of agro for that insane damage, although I wouldn't ever suggest it to VI and cry nerf. The fact you have to get a load of AA for this ability, well, that's irrelevant really. I'd gladly do 40 AA points to be able to outdamage a rogue by a large margin, even if it means I can only do it in 30% of the cases.<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I play both, a Ranger and Monk, depending on what I feel like or what my guild needs for their raid.  Ranger's are almost never in the exp group or rarely see exp for that matter in a raid.  In the 30% of the cases where we do use our archery it's only good for 2 minutes, the length of our trueshot, then archery is worthless again and we must go back into melee.  Timer before I can reuse it is 72 minutes so I am not as much of a damage dealer as you say, and since I only get two or three good hits, 20 miss's, and a bunch of hits for 8 to 100 points, I'd be better off meleeing, lord know's it's cheaper to melee then it is to make those arrows.  <br>
<br>
Just wanted to get the fact's straight before you go off overexhagerating about other class abilities.  As for the monk changes, I created my monk because he can tank better then my ranger, which honestly doesn't make sence when you compare leather to chainmail but it seems VI thinks leather is better.  I made a good friend who is a cleric and we worked our way from LOIO, level 15, all the way up to level 45 together before she quite playing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I hope the changes aren't as bad as to us resorting to full groups because the exp in full groups stink compaired to that of soloing and partnering, but I'm not gonna jinx myself till after the patch, it might not be as bad as some of us think. <br>
